        <p>However, much like the <a class="anchor-body" href="/case-studies/groups-ps" target="_blank">Panel Summary</a>, this email left much to be desired. It was hard to parse. At times it had too much information and other times not enough, and it wasn't interactive or trackable. Staff would print it out to get a better handle on it, and physically cross tasks off as they completed them. They were only able to see their own task list, which made it very difficult to cover for others if they needed to. There was also no tracking or sense of progress to share with their managers or other teammates. This lack of transparency made it difficult to work together to ensure members are getting the uninterrupted care and attention they need.</p>


