        <p>I showed these designs in another round of staff user interviews and they were delighted by its simplicity and power. They were excited by the robust filters, as well as the ability to expand tasks to see more information about the member and the task itself. Each task now has a history timeline to keep track of reassignments and questions, as well when a task is completed. Staff and their managers were happy about this accountability and transparency, and all this new functionality helped them realize that the Action List does in fact belong in the Digital Platform, and not in an email. This realization was a win, because it meant that they saw and understood the reason for the workflow change ‚Äì which is something that's usually met with resistance. I was happy to have their support as we rolled this out in a pilot program.</p>

