        <h3 class="article__heading">03. Outcome</h3>

        <p>We released the Action List to a small subset of office managers and counselors and had them use it as part of their daily workflow for two months. During that time I conducted another round of interviews to hear about their experience using it and any adjustments we should make before releasing it to the rest of the staff. They talked about the difficulty of adapting a new routine and nuances around particular workflows at Groups, but overall the feedback was positive and there were no huge UI changes to be made. After the pilot ended we released it to the team at large and sunsetted the email.</p>

        <p>This redesign was a huge win for our product team, which was reflected in the feedback survey we sent out a couple weeks after its release. We received overwhelmingly positive responses, with 92% of staff saying that the new Action List is easy to use, with its organization and sense of accomplishment being the things they valued most.</p>

